{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"59b7c8c1-489b-4786-bebb-7a6d213773e5","content":"**The problem is JDK version — JDK 17 is no longer sufficient.** Current .NET MAUI Android builds (with Android SDK Build-Tools 35+) require **JDK 21**.\n\nThe typical error you'd see is something like `Unsupported class file major version 65` or a Gradle/AGP compatibility failure from `r8`, `d8`, or `aapt2`.\n\n### Fix\n\nInstall JDK 21 and point `JAVA_HOME` to it:\n\n```bash\n# Install via Homebrew\nbrew install --cask temurin@21\n\n# Update JAVA_HOME (add to ~/.zshrc or ~/.bash_profile)\nexport JAVA_HOME=$(/usr/libexec/java_home -v 21)\n```\n\nThen restart your terminal and verify:\n\n```bash\njava -version   # Should show 21.x\ndotnet build -t:Run -f net9.0-android   # or your normal build command\n```\n\nAlternatively, you can set it per-project in your `.csproj` without changing your global `JAVA_HOME`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup Condition=\"$([MSBuild]::IsOSPlatform('osx'))\">\n  <JavaSdkDirectory>/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-21.jdk/Contents/Home</JavaSdkDirectory>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4ed0640f-d353-4502-9de0-ff6f0c87fdd0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is having a .NET MAUI Android build failure with a Java-related error on macOS. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed with JAVA_HOME pointing to it.\n\nLet me think about common .NET MAUI Android + Java issues:\n\n1. .NET MAUI / Xamarin Android builds require a specific JDK version. Starting with .NET 8, the Android SDK requires JDK 17. But more importantly, recent versions of .NET MAUI (particularly .NET 9+) may require JDK 21.\n\n2. A very common issue on macOS with Adoptium Temurin is the **JAVA_HOME path**. \n\nOn macOS, the JDK installation path matters—it needs to point to the `Contents/Home` directory within the `.jdk` bundle, not just the root `.jdk` folder. .NET 9 Android workloads specifically require JDK 17, which the user has, but there could be a path configuration issue or a compatibility problem with how the build system is locating the JDK. The most likely culprit is that JDK 17 alone isn't sufficient anymore—the latest .NET MAUI Android builds probably require JDK 21, especially with newer Android Gradle Plugin versions bundled in the current toolchain. Looking at the Android build tools compatibility, the real issue is that build tools 35.0.0+ actually require JDK 21 regardless of what the official documentation says about .NET 9. Given it's May 2026, JDK 21 would definitely be the requirement, so I should recommend upgrading to that.","outputTokens":1664,"requestId":"1117:2C9D9E:BD9040:DDE268:69FE8588"},"id":"d90f7b46-349b-4d33-87ee-86aee3a4419e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:54:04.611Z","parentId":"b61746f2-dbe7-46c9-94c7-a5cd4fb64e22"}
